        <h1>${CMAKE_PROJECT_NAME} v.${PROJECT_VERSION}</h1>
        <h2>${CMAKE_PROJECT_DESCRIPTION}</h2>

        <h3>TerraTech generates world maps for you</h3>
        <p>
            TerraTech provides a simple interface to generate world maps. The library is targetted at a video game development audience.
            But can be used in various environment
        </p>

        <h3>TerraTech is multi-platforms</h3>
        <p>
            TerraTech compiles and runs on various platforms. Our top tier supported platforms are:
            <ul>
                <li>Linux</li>
                <li>Mac OS X</li>
                <li>Windows</li>
            </ul>
            These are our top tiers because we assure that the code compile on these platforms.
        </p>

        <h3>TerraTech is multi-languages</h3>
        <p>
            TerraTech exposes a C-ANSI API. Thanks to that, the library can be used from any languages supporting FFI.
        </p>

